{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":600,"text":"When you come to TEDx,\nyou always think about technology,"},{"time":3320,"text":"the world changing,\nbecoming more innovative."},{"time":5680,"text":"You think about the driverless."},{"time":7480,"text":"Everyone's talking\nabout driverless cars these days,"},{"time":10920,"text":"and I love the concept\nof a driverless car,"},{"time":14040,"text":"but when I go in one, you know,"},{"time":17560,"text":"I want it really slow,"},{"time":20240,"text":"I want access to the steering wheel\nand the brake, just in case."},{"time":25720,"text":"I don't know about you,\nbut I am not ready for a driverless bus."},{"time":30560,"text":"I am not ready for a driverless airplane."}]},{"cues":[{"time":34520,"text":"How about a driverless world?"},{"time":38000,"text":"And I ask you that"},{"time":40440,"text":"because we are increasingly in one."}]},{"cues":[{"time":44800,"text":"It's not supposed to be that way."},{"time":46800,"text":"We're number one,"},{"time":48600,"text":"the United States is large and in charge."},{"time":52520,"text":"Americanization and globalization\nfor the last several generations"},{"time":57360,"text":"have basically been the same thing."},{"time":60040,"text":"Right? Whether it's\nthe World Trade Organization"},{"time":63880,"text":"or it's the IMF, the World Bank,"},{"time":66240,"text":"the Bretton Woods Accord on currency,"},{"time":68100,"text":"these were American institutions,"},{"time":69880,"text":"our values, our friends, our allies,\nour money, our standards."},{"time":74520,"text":"That was the way the world worked."}]},{"cues":[{"time":78280,"text":"So it's sort of interesting,\nif you want to look at how the US looks,"},{"time":83200,"text":"here it is."},{"time":84440,"text":"This is our view of how the world is run."},{"time":87760,"text":"President Obama has got the red carpet,"},{"time":90600,"text":"he goes down Air Force One,"},{"time":92440,"text":"and it feels pretty good,\nit feels pretty comfortable."},{"time":95000,"text":"Well, I don't know how many of you\nsaw the China trip last week"},{"time":98640,"text":"and the G20."},{"time":100720,"text":"Oh my God. Right?"},{"time":102960,"text":"This is how we landed"},{"time":104640,"text":"for the most important meeting\nof the world's leaders in China."},{"time":108160,"text":"The National Security Advisor\nwas actually spewing expletives"},{"time":112160,"text":"on the tarmac --"},{"time":114000,"text":"no red carpet,"},{"time":115440,"text":"kind of left out the bottom of the plane"},{"time":118120,"text":"along with all the media\nand everybody else."}]},{"cues":[{"time":121920,"text":"Later on in the G20,"},{"time":123920,"text":"well, there's Obama."}]},{"cues":[{"time":126360,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":127720,"text":"Hi, George."},{"time":129360,"text":"Hi, Norman."},{"time":132480,"text":"They look like they're\nabout to get into a cage match, right?"},{"time":136240,"text":"And they did. It was 90 minutes long,\nand they talked about Syria."},{"time":139360,"text":"That's what Putin wanted to talk about."},{"time":141280,"text":"He's increasingly calling the shots."},{"time":143040,"text":"He's the one willing to do stuff there."},{"time":145680,"text":"There's not a lot of mutual like or trust,"},{"time":149880,"text":"but it's not as if the Americans\nare telling him what to do."}]},{"cues":[{"time":152760,"text":"How about when the whole 20\nare getting together?"},{"time":155120,"text":"Surely, when the leaders are all onstage,"},{"time":157097,"text":"then the Americans\nare pulling their weight."},{"time":159200,"text":"Uh-oh."}]},{"cues":[{"time":160640,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":163760,"text":"Xi Jinping seems fine."},{"time":166880,"text":"Angela Merkel has -- she always does --"},{"time":168800,"text":"that look, she always does that."},{"time":171200,"text":"But Putin is telling\nTurkish president Erdogan what to do,"},{"time":174240,"text":"and Obama is like,\nwhat's going on over there?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":179840,"text":"You see. And the problem is\nit's not a G20,"},{"time":183200,"text":"the problem is"},{"time":184440,"text":"it's a G-Zero world that we live in,"},{"time":187440,"text":"a world order where there is\nno single country or alliance"},{"time":191880,"text":"that can meet the challenges\nof global leadership."},{"time":195280,"text":"The G20 doesn't work,"},{"time":197880,"text":"the G7, all of our friends,\nthat's history."},{"time":202000,"text":"So globalization is continuing."},{"time":204400,"text":"Goods and services and people\nand capital are moving across borders"},{"time":208080,"text":"faster and faster than ever before,"},{"time":210120,"text":"but Americanization is not."}]},{"cues":[{"time":213840,"text":"So if I've convinced you of that,"},{"time":215480,"text":"I want to do two things\nwith the rest of this talk."},{"time":218240,"text":"I want to talk\nabout the implications of that"},{"time":221720,"text":"for the whole world."},{"time":223000,"text":"I'll go around it."},{"time":224560,"text":"And then I want to talk about"},{"time":226200,"text":"what we think right here"},{"time":229120,"text":"in the United States and in New York."}]},{"cues":[{"time":232560,"text":"So why? What are the implications.\nWhy are we here?"},{"time":235200,"text":"Well, we're here"},{"time":237040,"text":"because the United States,"},{"time":240440,"text":"we spent two trillion dollars\non wars in Iraq and Afghanistan"},{"time":244280,"text":"that were failed."},{"time":245520,"text":"We don't want to do that anymore."},{"time":247160,"text":"We have large numbers\nof middle and working classes"},{"time":250840,"text":"that feel like they've not benefited\nfrom promises of globalization,"},{"time":254960,"text":"so they don't want to see it particularly."},{"time":257640,"text":"And we have an energy revolution"},{"time":260320,"text":"where we don't need OPEC\nor the Middle East the way we used to."},{"time":263520,"text":"We produce all that right here\nin the United States."},{"time":266000,"text":"So the Americans don't want\nto be the global sheriff for security"},{"time":271360,"text":"or the architect of global trade."},{"time":273680,"text":"The Americans don't want to even be\nthe cheerleader of global values."}]},{"cues":[{"time":277120,"text":"Well, then you look to Europe,"},{"time":280800,"text":"and the most important\nalliance in the world"},{"time":282920,"text":"has been the transatlantic relationship."},{"time":285680,"text":"But it is now weaker than it has been\nat any point since World War II,"},{"time":290080,"text":"all of the crises,\nthe Brexit conversations,"},{"time":292680,"text":"the hedging going on\nbetween the French and the Russians,"},{"time":296800,"text":"or the Germans and the Turks,\nor the Brits and the Chinese."}]},{"cues":[{"time":301000,"text":"China does want to do more leadership."},{"time":302960,"text":"They do, but only in the economic sphere,"},{"time":306000,"text":"and they want their own values,\nstandards, currency,"},{"time":309120,"text":"in competition with that of the US."},{"time":311240,"text":"The Russians want to do more leadership."},{"time":313200,"text":"You see that in Ukraine,"},{"time":315280,"text":"in the Baltic states, in the Middle East,"},{"time":318160,"text":"but not with the Americans."},{"time":319920,"text":"They want their own preferences and order."},{"time":322560,"text":"That's why we are where we are."}]},{"cues":[{"time":325480,"text":"So what happens going forward?"},{"time":328800,"text":"Let's start easy,"},{"time":330960,"text":"with the Middle East."}]},{"cues":[{"time":333160,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":336560,"text":"You know, I left a little out,"},{"time":339200,"text":"but you get the general idea."},{"time":342560,"text":"Look, there are three reasons"},{"time":344000,"text":"why the Middle East\nhas had stability such as it is. Right?"},{"time":349080,"text":"One is because there was\na willingness to provide"},{"time":353200,"text":"some level of military security\nby the US and allies."},{"time":356600,"text":"Number two, it was easy to take\na lot of cheap money out of the ground"},{"time":361280,"text":"because oil was expensive."},{"time":363080,"text":"And number three"},{"time":364440,"text":"was no matter how bad the leaders were,\nthe populations were relatively quiescent."},{"time":369560,"text":"They didn't have the ability,\nand many didn't have the will"},{"time":372360,"text":"to really rise up against."}]},{"cues":[{"time":373840,"text":"Well, I can tell you, in a G-Zero world,"},{"time":376400,"text":"all three of those things\nare increasingly not true,"},{"time":380040,"text":"and so failed states,"},{"time":382400,"text":"terrorism, refugees and the rest."},{"time":385640,"text":"Does the entire Middle East fall apart?"},{"time":387600,"text":"No, the Kurds will do better,\nand Iraq, Israel, Iran over time."},{"time":391480,"text":"But generally speaking,\nit's not a good look."}]},{"cues":[{"time":393880,"text":"OK, how about this guy?"},{"time":397280,"text":"He's playing a poor hand very well."},{"time":399760,"text":"There's no question\nhe's hitting above his weight."},{"time":402680,"text":"But long term -- I didn't mean that."},{"time":405960,"text":"But long term, long term,"},{"time":410280,"text":"if you think that the Russians"},{"time":411960,"text":"were antagonized by the US and Europe\nexpanding NATO right up to their borders"},{"time":417600,"text":"when we said they weren't going to,"},{"time":419270,"text":"and the EU encroaching them,"},{"time":421680,"text":"just wait until the Chinese\nput hundreds of billions of dollars"},{"time":425160,"text":"in every country around Russia\nthey thought they had influence in."},{"time":428320,"text":"The Chinese are going to dominate it.\nThe Russians are picking up the crumbs."},{"time":432000,"text":"In a G-Zero world, this is going to be\na very tense 10 years for Mr. Putin."}]},{"cues":[{"time":441040,"text":"It's not all bad. Right?"},{"time":443720,"text":"Asia actually looks a lot better."},{"time":446000,"text":"There are real leaders across Asia,"},{"time":449200,"text":"they have a lot of political stability."},{"time":451600,"text":"They're there for a while."},{"time":452880,"text":"Mr. Modi in India,"},{"time":455160,"text":"Mr. Abe, who is probably\nabout to get a third term written in"},{"time":459160,"text":"in the Liberal Democratic Party in Japan,"},{"time":461160,"text":"of course Xi Jinping\nwho is consolidating enormous power,"},{"time":464320,"text":"the most powerful leader in China"},{"time":466680,"text":"since Mao."},{"time":468360,"text":"Those are the three\nmost important economies in Asia."},{"time":471600,"text":"Now look, there are problems in Asia."},{"time":473440,"text":"We see the sparring\nover the South China Sea."},{"time":476120,"text":"We see that Kim Jong Un,\njust in the last couple of days,"},{"time":478840,"text":"tested yet another nuclear weapon."},{"time":482040,"text":"But the leaders in Asia\ndo not feel the need"},{"time":486320,"text":"to wave the flag,"},{"time":487880,"text":"to go xenophobic,"},{"time":489720,"text":"to actually allow escalation"},{"time":492800,"text":"of the geopolitical\nand cross-border tensions."},{"time":495320,"text":"They want to focus on long-term\neconomic stability and growth."},{"time":500720,"text":"And that's what they're actually doing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":503600,"text":"Let's turn to Europe."},{"time":506320,"text":"Europe does look a little scared\nin this environment."},{"time":508920,"text":"So much of what is happening\nin the Middle East"},{"time":511240,"text":"is washing up quite literally\nonto European shores."},{"time":516000,"text":"You see Brexit and you see\nthe concerns of populism"},{"time":519799,"text":"across all of the European states."}]},{"cues":[{"time":523400,"text":"Let me tell you that over the long term,"},{"time":526080,"text":"in a G-Zero world,"},{"time":527880,"text":"European expansion\nwill be seen to have gone too far."},{"time":532520,"text":"Europe went right up to Russia,\nwent right down to the Middle East,"},{"time":536320,"text":"and if the world were truly becoming\nmore flat and more Americanized,"},{"time":540600,"text":"that would be less of a problem,"},{"time":542200,"text":"but in a G-Zero world,\nthose countries nearest Russia"},{"time":545720,"text":"and nearest the Middle East"},{"time":547360,"text":"actually have different\neconomic capabilities,"},{"time":550760,"text":"different social stability"},{"time":552600,"text":"and different political preferences\nand systems than core Europe."},{"time":556800,"text":"So Europe was able to truly expand"},{"time":559840,"text":"under the G7,"},{"time":561920,"text":"but under the G-Zero,\nEurope will get smaller."},{"time":564480,"text":"Core Europe around Germany\nand France and others"},{"time":568520,"text":"will still work, be functional,\nstable, wealthy, integrated."},{"time":572600,"text":"But the periphery,"},{"time":574040,"text":"countries like Greece\nand Turkey and others,"},{"time":576520,"text":"will not look that good at all."}]},{"cues":[{"time":580200,"text":"Latin America, a lot of populism,"},{"time":583600,"text":"made the economies not go so well."},{"time":585640,"text":"They had been more opposed\nto the United States for decades."},{"time":588520,"text":"Increasingly, they're coming back."},{"time":590480,"text":"We see that in Argentina."},{"time":592160,"text":"We see it with the openness in Cuba."},{"time":593920,"text":"We will see it in Venezuela\nwhen Maduro falls."},{"time":597160,"text":"We will see it in Brazil\nafter the impeachment"},{"time":600200,"text":"and when we finally see\na new legitimate president elected there."},{"time":604720,"text":"The only place you see\nthat is moving in another direction"},{"time":607840,"text":"is the unpopularity\nof Mexican president Peña Nieto."},{"time":611440,"text":"There you could actually see\na slip away from the United States"},{"time":615320,"text":"over the coming years."},{"time":616600,"text":"The US election matters a lot\non that one, too."}]},{"cues":[{"time":619640,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":621600,"text":"Africa, right?"},{"time":623440,"text":"A lot of people have said\nit's going to be Africa's decade, finally."},{"time":626680,"text":"In a G-Zero world,\nit is absolutely an amazing time"},{"time":630240,"text":"for a few African countries,"},{"time":632000,"text":"those governed well\nwith a lot of urbanization,"},{"time":634680,"text":"a lot of smart people,\nwomen really getting into the workforce,"},{"time":638200,"text":"entrepreneurship taking off."},{"time":640200,"text":"But for most of the countries in Africa,"},{"time":643000,"text":"it's going to be a lot more dicey:"},{"time":644920,"text":"extreme climate conditions,"},{"time":647960,"text":"radicalism both from Islam\nand also Christianity,"},{"time":652200,"text":"very poor governance,"},{"time":653640,"text":"borders you can't defend,\nlots of forced migration."},{"time":656680,"text":"Those countries can fall off the map."},{"time":658800,"text":"So you're really going to see\nan extreme segregation going on"},{"time":662560,"text":"between the winners\nand the losers across Africa."}]},{"cues":[{"time":665920,"text":"Finally, back to the United States."},{"time":669840,"text":"What do I think about us?"},{"time":672480,"text":"Because there are a lot of upset people,"},{"time":675240,"text":"not here at TEDx, I know,"},{"time":677920,"text":"but in the United States, my God,"},{"time":679720,"text":"after 15 months of campaigning,\nwe should be upset."},{"time":682200,"text":"I understand that."},{"time":684200,"text":"But a lot of people are upset\nbecause they say, \"Washington's broken,"},{"time":687480,"text":"we don't trust the establishment,\nwe hate the media.\""},{"time":690000,"text":"Heck, even globalists like me\nare taking it on the chin."}]},{"cues":[{"time":694160,"text":"Look, I do think we have to recognize,"},{"time":698800,"text":"my fellow campers,"},{"time":701040,"text":"that when you are being\nchased by the bear,"},{"time":705480,"text":"in the global context,\nyou need not outrun the bear,"},{"time":709800,"text":"you need to only outrun\nyour fellow campers."}]},{"cues":[{"time":712440,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":715720,"text":"Now, I just told you"},{"time":717880,"text":"about our fellow campers."},{"time":720000,"text":"Right? And from that perspective,"},{"time":722960,"text":"we look OK."},{"time":725000,"text":"A lot of people in that context say,"},{"time":727040,"text":"\"Let's go dollar.\nLet's go New York real estate."},{"time":730560,"text":"Let's send our kids\nto American universities.\""},{"time":733640,"text":"You know, our neighbors are awesome:"},{"time":735800,"text":"Canada, Mexico\nand two big bodies of water."},{"time":738680,"text":"You know how much Turkey\nwould love to have neighbors like that?"},{"time":743080,"text":"Those are awesome neighbors."}]},{"cues":[{"time":746400,"text":"Terrorism is a problem\nin the United States."},{"time":748720,"text":"God knows we know it here in New York."},{"time":752040,"text":"But it's a much bigger problem\nin Europe than the US."},{"time":754541,"text":"It's a much bigger problem\nin the Middle East"},{"time":756880,"text":"than it is in Europe."},{"time":758480,"text":"These are factors of large magnitude."},{"time":760640,"text":"We just accepted 10,000 Syrian refugees,\nand we're complaining bitterly about it."},{"time":765640,"text":"You know why?\nBecause they can't swim here."},{"time":768480,"text":"Right? I mean, the Turks would love\nto have only 10,000 Syrian refugees."},{"time":773200,"text":"The Jordanians,\nthe Germans, the Brits. Right?"},{"time":776520,"text":"That's not the situation."},{"time":777800,"text":"That's the reality of the United States."}]},{"cues":[{"time":781000,"text":"Now, that sounds pretty good."},{"time":784440,"text":"Here's the challenge."},{"time":786600,"text":"In a G-Zero world, the way you lead"},{"time":790640,"text":"is by example."},{"time":792240,"text":"If we know we don't want to be\nthe global cop anymore,"},{"time":795280,"text":"if we know we're not going to be\nthe architect of global trade,"},{"time":798257,"text":"we're not going to be\nthe cheerleader of global values,"},{"time":800880,"text":"we're not going to do it\nthe way we used to,"},{"time":803000,"text":"the 21st century is changing,"},{"time":804405,"text":"we need to lead by example --\nbe so compelling"},{"time":807280,"text":"that all these other people\nare going to still say,"},{"time":809720,"text":"it's not just they're faster campers."},{"time":811560,"text":"Even when the bear is not chasing us,\nthis is a good place to be."},{"time":814680,"text":"We want to emulate them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":816880,"text":"The election process this year\nis not proving a good option"},{"time":822040,"text":"for leading by example."},{"time":824640,"text":"Hillary Clinton says\nit's going to be like the '90s."},{"time":827120,"text":"We can still be\nthat cheerleader on values."},{"time":830080,"text":"We can still be\nthe architect of global trade."},{"time":832600,"text":"We can still be the global sheriff."},{"time":834320,"text":"And Donald Trump wants\nto bring us back to the '30s."},{"time":838560,"text":"He's saying, \"Our way or the highway.\nYou don't like it, lump it.\" Right?"},{"time":842520,"text":"Neither are recognizing\na fundamental truth of the G-Zero,"},{"time":846400,"text":"which is that even though\nthe US is not in decline,"},{"time":850200,"text":"it is getting objectively harder"},{"time":852760,"text":"for the Americans to impose their will,"},{"time":855960,"text":"even have great influence,"},{"time":857680,"text":"on the global order."}]},{"cues":[{"time":860280,"text":"Are we prepared to truly lead by example?"},{"time":864200,"text":"What would we have to do to fix this"},{"time":867280,"text":"after November,"},{"time":868520,"text":"after the next president comes in?"},{"time":870720,"text":"Well, either we have to have\nanother crisis that forces us to respond."},{"time":875400,"text":"A depression would do that."},{"time":877080,"text":"Another global financial\ncrisis could do this."},{"time":879280,"text":"God forbid, another 9/11 could do that."},{"time":881320,"text":"Or, absent crisis,"},{"time":883800,"text":"we need to see that the hollowing out,\nthe inequality, the challenges"},{"time":889960,"text":"that are growing and growing\nin the United States,"},{"time":892360,"text":"are themselves urgent enough"},{"time":894560,"text":"to force our leaders to change,"},{"time":896920,"text":"and that we have those voices."},{"time":899400,"text":"Through our cell phones, individually,"},{"time":901320,"text":"we have those voices\nto compel them to change."}]},{"cues":[{"time":905480,"text":"There is, of course, a third choice,"},{"time":908200,"text":"perhaps the most likely one,"},{"time":910200,"text":"which is that we do\nneither of those things,"},{"time":912920,"text":"and in four years time you invite me back,"},{"time":915520,"text":"and I will give this speech yet again."}]},{"cues":[{"time":918320,"text":"Thank you very, very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":920200,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}